The Doctor SickleCell Centre For Sickle Cell Disease in association with Olusegun Obasanjo Foundation has concluded plans to hold intervention programs for sickle cell disorder in Africa. Speaking ahead of the African Congress on Sickle Cell Disease, ACSCD slated for 31 October to 2nd November in Lagos, ACSCD Co-chair Dr. David Ajaere said that the program seek to address the challenges of the disorder and foster possible solutions to its effect as a public health burden. He explained that the conference will also facilitate exchange of information among public health experts, medical professionals, researchers, policy-makers, key stakeholders to highlight challenges and opportunities and enhance strategies to control Sickle Cell Disease in Africa<img class="alignnone wp-image-1224529 size-full" src="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Nigeria-Healthcare-Excellence.jpeg?resize=640%2C520&#038;ssl=1" alt="Nigeria,Sickle Cell" width="640" height="520" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Nigeria-Healthcare-Excellence.jpeg?w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Nigeria-Healthcare-Excellence.jpeg?resize=300%2C244&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Nigeria-Healthcare-Excellence.jpeg?resize=768%2C624&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Nigeria-Healthcare-Excellence.jpeg?resize=1024%2C832&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Nigeria-Healthcare-Excellence.jpeg?resize=58%2C47&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Nigeria-Healthcare-Excellence.jpeg?resize=239%2C194&amp;ssl=1 239w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Nigeria-Healthcare-Excellence.jpeg?resize=160%2C130&amp;ssl=1 160w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Nigeria-Health